com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto

Interface IItemUpdateReport

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IItemBaseReport

    public interface IItemUpdateReport
extends IItemBaseReport
    A description of how a single item was affected.

    The effect on a particular item is described in terms of 2 states (not necessarily distinct). This is sufficient to describe any possible outcome of a successful update without prejudice as to which particular result a particular server would apply in a particular instance. It's important that the client make no unwarranted assumptions about how an item will be affected.

    Unopposed incoming change: closed A:1->2; active: none; incoming: A:2->3
    This is a straightforward case of an incoming change set advancing the state of an item. The result would typically be
    closed A:1->2,2->3; active: none. That is, the change is accepted into the workspace with the result that the current state of the item is advanced. This outcome would be described as follows: getPreviousState() is 2; getNewCurrentState() is 3.

    0.5

        IComponentHandle getPriorComponent()
